text.tspan: Per capita nitrous oxide emissions from agriculture
Nitrous oxide (N₂O) emissions are measured in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalents (CO₂e), based on 100-year
global warming potential factors for non-CO₂ gases.
Source: Our World in Data based on Climate Analysis Indicators Tool (CAIT).
